# Migration Module Patterns

## Two initialization modes

The `Migration` class supports two ways to connect to source and target environments:

```python
# YAML config files
m = Migration(source_yaml="source.yaml", target_yaml="target.yaml", debug=False)

# Agent-friendly: pass SisenseClient instances directly
m = Migration(source_client=src, target_client=tgt)
```

## Progress reporting via `_emit`

Use the `_emit(message)` callback for progress reporting. Set it at init or as an attribute. Defaults to `print`.

```python
m = Migration(source_client=src, target_client=tgt)
m._emit = my_progress_callback
```

## Migration order matters

Dependencies must be migrated before the objects that reference them:
1. Groups first
2. Users (reference groups)
3. Data models (referenced by dashboards)
4. Dashboards last (reference users, groups, data models)

## YAML config format

```yaml
# source.yaml / target.yaml
domain: your-sisense-instance.com
token: your-api-token
is_ssl: true
```
